  "A break-in takes about 90 seconds, and the single biggest deterrent is a camera an intruder can actually see. The problem is that most security cameras mean drilling, running cable, or climbing a ladder every few months to recharge a battery — so a lot of people never get around to it.",
  "Light-socket cameras solve that. They screw into an existing light fitting, draw power from it permanently, and light the area they're watching. We compared the leading options available in Australia on verified customer ratings, resolution, night vision, power and value.",
  "Here are the top 5 of the year, with a full review of our #1 pick further down the page.",
];

const deepDive = {
  heading: "Why the HauSafe Cam HD Is Our #1 Pick",
  body: [
    "The HauSafe wins on the thing that actually determines whether a camera protects your home: whether it ever gets installed. It screws into a standard light socket like a bulb. No drilling, no wiring, no mounting bracket, no electrician — you stand on a chair, twist it in, and it's live.",
